race.description: Merry Christmas And Happy New Year Handicap (55)
race.comment: STANDLEE (4) is a talented type yet to taste defeat after two runs this campaign, the latest over 1350m at Ipswich. Can't knock current form and he will run well again. SEACRYPTION (12) doesn't win out of turn but won't have to improve much to be fighting out the finish this time. Draws to get the gun run and keeps the claimer. Gets her chance to break a long run of outs. SHOT DOWN BY LOVE (10) was a big improver here second-up when arriving just in time to score. Fitter again and the mile should suit. Can make it two on the bounce. GOT YOURSELF A GUN (1) hasn't looked likely in his two runs back after settling a long way of them. Strips fitter third-up and should find this easier. Watch for him if he's close enough when straightening.
